1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,139
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,223 --> 00:00:16,808
<i>Terrace House</i> is a show about
six strangers, men and women,

3
00:00:16,892 --> 00:00:18,435
6 STRANGERS, MEN AND WOMEN,
SHARE A HOUSE.

4
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:21,188
living together, and we observe
how they interact with each other.

5
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:23,899
<i>All that we've prepared is</i>
<i>a beautiful home and automobile.</i>

6
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:26,610
-There is no script at all.
-Yes.

7
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:30,906
So last week,
the meat incident continued.

8
00:00:30,989 --> 00:00:33,659
That's right.
Another crisis on top of everything.

9
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:36,495
Tatsuya's breakdown.

10
00:00:36,578 --> 00:00:42,000
TATSUYA UCHIHARA, 24 YEARS OLD
MINORI NAKADA, 21 YEARS OLD

11
00:00:42,084 --> 00:00:43,252
Why are you crying?

12
00:00:43,335 --> 00:00:45,295
Everything I've held back until now
broke loose.

13
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:47,756
From this shared living situation.

14
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:51,593
A lot has happened
and all he's held back finally exploded.

15
00:00:51,677 --> 00:00:53,887
-An accumulation.
-Yes, that's right.

16
00:00:53,971 --> 00:00:55,722
Who knew the meat crime
would come this far.

17
00:00:55,806 --> 00:00:57,057
-That's right.
-That's true.

18
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:59,434
<i>-But they seemed to have made up.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

19
00:00:59,518 --> 00:01:00,852
<i>Problem solved.</i>

20
00:01:00,936 --> 00:01:02,104
<i>And Arman...</i>

21
00:01:02,187 --> 00:01:04,064
Seems to have started working.

22
00:01:04,147 --> 00:01:08,569
-And he went to Arisa...
-That's right.

23
00:01:08,652 --> 00:01:11,697
But if you feel something for me at all,

24
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:16,451
you could spare even ten minutes a day
to talk to me.

25
00:01:16,535 --> 00:01:17,703
That's what I think.

26
00:01:17,786 --> 00:01:20,872
So I wanted to ask one last time
how you feel about me.

27
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:24,293
I don't have time to think about
anything else right now.

28
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:25,836
ARISA OHATA, 25 YEARS OLD
ARMAN BITARAF, 25 YEARS OLD

29
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,087
I'm sorry.

30
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:29,506
<i>Arisa, when she first rejected him,</i>

31
00:01:29,589 --> 00:01:32,843
told him that she wasn't ready yet
but wanted to get to know him more.

32
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:36,346
She left him with false hope.

33
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:42,602
And Arman, holding on to that hope,
foolishly believed her.

34
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:44,896
Arisa made that happen.

35
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:46,440
She's at fault.

36
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:50,027
She tried to let him down nicely.

37
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:53,322
-The way she rejected him.
-Is that really niceness though?

38
00:01:53,405 --> 00:01:56,867
-No, I don't think it's nice at all.
-Yes, that's exactly right!

39
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,702
In my opinion, anyway.

40
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:00,495
-She completely betrayed me.
-You?

41
00:02:00,579 --> 00:02:04,124
Yes.
We were on the same wavelength.

42
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:07,044
You've never been on the same wavelength.

43
00:02:07,127 --> 00:02:09,004
Will you stop saying "creepy"
under your breath?

44
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:12,966
You think you're better than me,
don't you?

45
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,971
Well... shall we continue?

46
00:02:18,055 --> 00:02:20,432
-Can I just say one more thing?
-What?

47
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,808
Thanks to everyone,

48
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:27,731
I've been commissioned
to do a commercial for Netflix.

49
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,359
And there's even
a kissing scene with an actress.

50
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:32,861
-We just filmed it.
-What?

51
00:02:32,944 --> 00:02:33,945
You kissed?

52
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:35,405
-We kissed.
-What?

53
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:38,784
I play the role of her boyfriend
and she's completely into me.

54
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:42,454
-Well, it's her job.
-You mean within her role.

55
00:02:42,537 --> 00:02:43,914
I know it's terrible,

56
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:46,041
but because of some bad takes
of the kiss scene,

57
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:47,751
I delayed production by three hours.

58
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,045
What?
How many bad takes were there?

59
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:53,757
I'm supposed to lay there
and then react nonchalantly to the kiss.

60
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,759
But I'd get so nervous,
and I'd be like...

61
00:02:57,636 --> 00:03:00,972
Do you think
the actress was upset with me?

62
00:03:01,056 --> 00:03:03,475
Upset? No.
Maybe grossed out.

63
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:10,690
I understand being nervous about the job.

64
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:14,444
But you just do it.
You just do as you're told.

65
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:17,697
I can't emotionally detach myself
from a kiss yet.

66
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:20,492
I'm sure the actress would prefer it...

67
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,994
-if you could detach yourself.
-Otherwise, it's gross.

68
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:29,334
Your mom isn't here today.

69
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:37,217
PUKUICHI

70
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:42,222
PUKUICHI
TORITSU DAIGAKU, TOKYO

71
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,810
-Hi.
-Hi!

72
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:49,730
-Were you able to find it easily?
-Yeah. It was close to the station.

73
00:03:49,813 --> 00:03:51,815
You've got full-on makeup today.

74
00:03:51,898 --> 00:03:53,942
I had work today.

75
00:03:55,694 --> 00:03:58,363
-Are you hungry?
-I am.

76
00:03:58,989 --> 00:04:00,532
The food here is super delicious.

77
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:03,910
-This is your friend's place?
-Yeah, it's my friend's place.

78
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:09,541
When I told everyone
you invited me out to dinner,

79
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:13,503
Uchi was like, "Seriously?"

80
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,047
He said you hardly invited anyone.

81
00:04:16,131 --> 00:04:17,799
Did it make you wonder why?

82
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,926
No, not really.

83
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:24,431
I was just thinking about
how I could get to know you.

84
00:04:25,140 --> 00:04:29,728
And that's when you invited me.

85
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:32,147
So it honestly made me happy.

86
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,482
-Really?
-Yeah.

87
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:35,609
Honestly.

88
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:42,616
After the meat incident,
did anything change between you and Uchi?

89
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,868
I think that it did.

90
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:49,998
We both talk to each other more now.

91
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:54,044
-I think we changed in a good way.
-I see.

92
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:56,588
-I'm happy for you.
-Yeah. Me too.

93
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:00,258
-I'm glad we ate the meat.
-That's so true.

94
00:05:00,342 --> 00:05:01,343
It ended well?

95
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:04,179
I don't know if Uchi feels the same,
but...

96
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:12,229
It's delicious.

97
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:13,772
Isn't it?
It's so good.

98
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:17,484
Totally off topic, but...

99
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,153
did you come to <i>Terrace House</i>
thinking you'd find love?

100
00:05:20,237 --> 00:05:22,364
-Not at all.
-I see.

101
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:25,826
I totally didn't think
it was a possibility.

102
00:05:25,909 --> 00:05:30,247
I want to find love,
but at <i>Terrace House...</i>

103
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:35,502
I don't know if I can.
I'm like you.

104
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:37,587
But you were saying yesterday...

105
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:42,384
about how Hikaru's great,
but his age...

106
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,470
-That, I don't get.
-Why?

107
00:05:45,554 --> 00:05:49,140
I've never dated or fallen in love
with someone younger.

108
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,477
I want to be the pampered one.

109
00:05:52,561 --> 00:05:56,773
And I feel like
I can't have that with someone younger.

110
00:05:56,856 --> 00:05:59,067
But that just depends on the guy's...

111
00:06:00,277 --> 00:06:01,945
ability.

112
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:08,410
I'm really glad that we went out today.

113
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,328
-Here.
-I'm glad.

114
00:06:15,584 --> 00:06:19,421
It is really nice
you have someone you love to give it to.

115
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:23,008
I'm pretty envious.

116
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:26,386
-He said he wants one from the store.
-Seriously?

117
00:06:26,469 --> 00:06:28,972
-He said he wants Godiva chocolates.
-That's terrible!

118
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:39,316
-Is it good? Hot?
-It's hot.

119
00:06:40,275 --> 00:06:42,819
It's hot! Hot! Hot!

120
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,780
It's good, but it's hot.

121
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,539
Look at that!

122
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:56,499
-It's cute!
-It's super cute!

123
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:01,004
-Happy Valentine's Day!
-Happy Valentine's!

124
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,089
Wow, they're all wrapped.

125
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:05,425
-Ta-da!
-Did you buy them?

126
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:07,927
No! We made them together.

127
00:07:08,011 --> 00:07:09,512
Woo!

128
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:12,599
-Yay!
-Wow.

129
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:15,268
-Yay, thanks!
-For Arman!

130
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:16,353
Wow! It's got my name on it.

131
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:18,730
-Are they all different?
-For Hikaru!

132
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,023
-Thanks.
-Happy Valentine's.

133
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,191
It says, "For you."

134
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:24,194
-This one's also for you.
-Yeah!

135
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:25,528
Take a look at this!

136
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:27,697
Don't you guys want to see?

137
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:30,742
-Hey, guys!
-You should see!

138
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:33,620
-Aren't you guys interested?
-It says "Hikaru" here.

139
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,121
They're ignoring us.

140
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:37,999
-Hey, mine's smaller.
-Hey, over here!

141
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,585
-I knew you'd notice.
-Look here.

142
00:07:40,669 --> 00:07:42,128
Is this, like, the leftover?

143
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,631
It's good.

144
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:46,633
-Yeah, it's a cookie.
-Yay!

145
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,802
-It's good.
-Thanks.

146
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:51,179
I'm sure Arisa has stuff for you, too.

147
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:52,514
Oh, Arisa...

148
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:56,017
-Is she coming back?
-Yeah.

149
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:57,936
She said she would be home late.

150
00:07:58,019 --> 00:07:59,813
I have an announcement.

151
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:03,108
What?

152
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:06,194
The morning of the 18th...

153
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,862
-we'll be leaving.
-What?

154
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:10,365
Why so sudden?

155
00:08:10,448 --> 00:08:11,908
You have to tell us earlier.

156
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,744
-That's why we're telling you early.
-There's still four days.

157
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:17,789
We were gonna say it yesterday,
but decided to wait for Arisa.

158
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:22,836
-What? This is so sad.
-Hikaru's about to cry.

159
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:24,838
I'm not, but...

160
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:27,924
I'm not. I'm not crying.

161
00:08:28,925 --> 00:08:30,969
So, the snowboarding trip
will be our goodbye trip.

162
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:32,095
I'm glad we're going snowboarding.

163
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:35,306
-Yeah, let's go have fun.
-You don't even know how to snowboard.

164
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,475
-I can't, but...
-Let's go have fun.

165
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,394
Everyone has scheduled to go snowboarding
except Natsumi.

166
00:08:42,397 --> 00:08:45,316
KAWABA SKI RESORT
TONE COUNTY, GUNMA

167
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:47,861
-Arman, you're going to wear sunglasses?
-Shouldn't I?

168
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:52,323
-Wow.
-It feels great!

169
00:08:54,659 --> 00:08:56,077
I hope I don't fall.

170
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:57,829
-Look out.
-Nice.

171
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,497
It's so beautiful.

172
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:02,125
-First snow of the season?
-First snow for the mountain.

173
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,263
How do I stop?

174
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:32,113
Then you lean forward, like this.

175
00:09:37,786 --> 00:09:40,330
