303
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:03,898
-It's good, right?
-Yeah, I'm envious.

304
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:07,235
What about your part-time job?

305
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:09,820
I'll continue working.

306
00:17:09,904 --> 00:17:11,614
-You will?
-Yeah.

307
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:16,452
I'll continue my other jobs, too.

308
00:17:16,536 --> 00:17:20,081
Only my living situation will change.

309
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:23,042
So that's okay.

310
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,835
I'm so excited.

311
00:17:24,919 --> 00:17:26,879
It's an unknown world.

312
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:32,593
The cafe in Asakusa you were working on...

313
00:17:32,677 --> 00:17:35,137
-did you finish that?
-Yeah, I'm done with that.

314
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:40,434
So when you have to work,
you're gonna work here?

315
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:44,021
Yeah, I'll work from here.

316
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:47,358
-You're gonna use it as your studio?
-Yeah.

317
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:54,115
We've had drinks together often,
but that's it for now.

318
00:17:54,198 --> 00:17:57,618
I'll be moving to <i>Terrace House.</i>

319
00:17:57,702 --> 00:18:00,705
What made you decide?

320
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,999
I'm graduating...

321
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:04,792
I figured it'd be a good change of pace.

322
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:08,713
But the people who are looking for working
in the entertainment industry

323
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:09,964
and the people who aren't

324
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:13,217
have completely different reasons
for joining <i>Terrace House.</i>

325
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:16,554
What are you looking to gain specifically?

326
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:19,890
I don't know what I'll gain.
I don't know what life there will be like.

327
00:18:19,974 --> 00:18:23,394
But there are more possibilities there
than if I stay here.

328
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,730
You're going to accept
both pros and cons?

329
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:30,318
Yeah, it wasn't a decision
based on logical reasoning.

330
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:32,194
It's more like an adventure.

331
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:38,993
It was nice at the end
for Minori and Natsumi...

332
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:41,370
They became close.

333
00:18:41,454 --> 00:18:46,042
It's been a while since we got to see
a harmonious <i>Terrace House.</i>

334
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:51,672
Now that they've overcome this together,
they may be really close for life.

335
00:18:51,756 --> 00:18:54,300
-Maybe.
-It's possible.

336
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:58,262
It reminds me of an old soap opera
with Akina Nakamori and Narumi Yasuda.

337
00:18:58,346 --> 00:19:01,015
-I've seen that.
<i>-Just the Way We Are!</i>

338
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,225
Yeah, it's like the two of them.

339
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:05,686
Natsumi is Akina Nakamori.

340
00:19:06,729 --> 00:19:07,730
That's right.

341
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:09,732
The song was, <i>Just by You Being Here.</i>

342
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:11,692
-By Kome Kome Club.
-Was it?

343
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:15,363
I bought the CD for my girlfriend then.

344
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:18,032
-Oh, I see.
-It brings back memories.

345
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:19,575
Saying, "It's just for you?"

346
00:19:22,078 --> 00:19:23,829
I've become so tainted.

347
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:29,168
-They're coming.
-The new members.

348
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:32,213
-The girl seems pretty.
-Totally beautiful!

349
00:19:32,296 --> 00:19:34,757
-This area of the pretty one...
-Yes, the face structure.

350
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:38,386
Is the guy in architecture school?

351
00:19:38,469 --> 00:19:40,304
Seemed like a group of creative types.

352
00:19:40,388 --> 00:19:42,640
-Maybe graphic--
-Didn't he mention graduating?

353
00:19:42,723 --> 00:19:45,267
-He seems put together.
-Yeah.

354
00:19:45,351 --> 00:19:46,519
I wonder.

355
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:49,355
It doesn't seem like he'd get along
with Arman and Hikaru.

356
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:51,315
I wonder.

357
00:19:51,399 --> 00:19:53,150
-Really, now.
-That's true.

358
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:56,445
-Just curry is fine, right?
-Yeah.

359
00:19:56,529 --> 00:19:59,740
-There's only four of us.
-That's true.

360
00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:03,577
-Can I switch this?
-Yeah, thanks.

361
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:16,549
Thank you.

362
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:18,134
"If you use it,
you should wash it right away."

363
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:20,136
That's my motto.

364
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,138
I see.

365
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:23,639
I see.

366
00:20:23,723 --> 00:20:26,475
-Is it ready?
-Doesn't chicken take a while to cook?

367
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:28,477
But we're gonna add water.

368
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:29,937
Oh, sorry.

369
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,272
I'm so hungry.

370
00:20:36,569 --> 00:20:37,695
Could it be...

371
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:40,239
It's happening now?

372
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,036
Hello.

373
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:48,164
<i>Hi, I'm moving in today.</i>

374
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:51,333
Please come in.

375
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:01,469
-It is a girl.
-I guess a girl is coming first.

376
00:21:02,553 --> 00:21:03,721
What?

377
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:07,892
Isn't it weird
that we're going to greet her here?

378
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:11,520
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

379
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:14,899
I'm Misaki Tamori.
It's nice to meet you.

380
00:21:14,982 --> 00:21:16,150
Nice to meet you, too.

381
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,445
-I'm sorry to greet you here.
-It's okay.

382
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,906
-We were cooking...
-What were you making?

383
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:24,909
Curry.
Let's eat together.

384
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:26,994
Thank you very much.

385
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,996
Of course.

386
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:32,249
-Should I sit down?
-Please sit.

387
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:35,169
-I'm sorry. What is your name again?
-I'm Misaki Tamori.

388
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:36,629
-Misaki?
-Misaki.

389
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:39,131
My friends call me Tamochan or Tamosan.

390
00:21:39,215 --> 00:21:40,257
Tamosan?

391
00:21:40,341 --> 00:21:42,927
-How old are you?
-I'm 23.

392
00:21:44,094 --> 00:21:45,888
What do you do?

393
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,266
I'm trying to break into the entertainment
industry, while working part-time jobs.

394
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:50,601
-A model?
-No.

395
00:21:50,684 --> 00:21:52,603
-More like variety shows.
-Oh, talent shows.

396
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:54,522
MISAKI TAMORI, 23 YEARS OLD
ASPIRING ENTERTAINER, PART-TIMER

397
00:21:54,605 --> 00:21:56,273
-Where are you from?
-From Hokkaido.

398
00:21:58,108 --> 00:22:00,486
-Do you have a boyfriend?
-I don't.

399
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:03,072
-How long since your last one?
-About a year.

400
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:04,448
Oh, we're the same.

401
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:07,910
It's like a dream.

402
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:12,540
I've always watched the show,
so it's strange to actually be here.

403
00:22:14,375 --> 00:22:17,002
How long have you lived here?

404
00:22:17,086 --> 00:22:19,505
A little over a month.

405
00:22:19,588 --> 00:22:23,217
-Did you have any trouble sleeping?
-Not at all.

406
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,553
-You too?
-Yeah.

407
00:22:25,636 --> 00:22:28,430
Do you tend to worry about little things?

408
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:30,266
-Not at all.
-Then you won't have trouble sleeping.

409
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:31,767
Not at all, huh?

410
00:22:31,850 --> 00:22:33,852
Not at all?
Do you like to clean?

411
00:22:33,936 --> 00:22:37,147
-Oh, no!
-You like to keep clean?

412
00:22:37,231 --> 00:22:39,316
Oh, no, something is bound to happen!

413
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,943
You don't keep tidy?

414
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,737
I'm not going to hold back. Is that okay?

415
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,323
But I might say something back.

416
00:22:46,407 --> 00:22:48,492
-This is gonna be good.
-Yeah.

417
00:22:48,576 --> 00:22:51,078
Like, "What's wrong with that?"

418
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:54,290
-Okay.
-Something that's the norm for me

419
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:56,292
might not be for someone who likes
to be clean.

420
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,877
For example, after you eat,
do you leave it behind?

421
00:22:58,961 --> 00:23:01,130
-I do.
-That's the norm?

422
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:03,674
-It's not, but...
-You might eat it later.

423
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:04,925
-Yeah.
-Yeah. I get it.

424
00:23:05,009 --> 00:23:06,969
-No, I meant trash.
-Yes, I leave it.

425
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:08,887
-Do you throw it out right away?
-No, later.

426
00:23:08,971 --> 00:23:10,347
Let's do it right away.

427
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:16,145
Oh, no! But I thought
maybe being here will make me better.

428
00:23:16,228 --> 00:23:18,272
Oh, then please do.

429
00:23:18,355 --> 00:23:21,483
-But I still might say something.
-Okay.

430
00:23:21,567 --> 00:23:24,445
So, have you asked?

431
00:23:24,528 --> 00:23:27,489
-What's your type? What kind of guy?
-Oh, my type?

432
00:23:27,573 --> 00:23:30,159
Someone who's considerate
of those around them.

433
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:32,578
And looks?

434
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:35,331
For looks, I'm not consistent.

435
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:38,751
I've dated guys
with both soft and welldefined features.

436
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:40,586
I don't have a specific type.

437
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:43,464
I think it's ready.

438
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,801
I wonder if we have enough roux?

439
00:23:48,802 --> 00:23:50,095
Oh, we haven't added it yet.

440
00:23:50,179 --> 00:23:52,222
Will you drink today?

441
00:23:52,306 --> 00:23:53,390
I will.

442
00:23:53,474 --> 00:23:54,642
Should we buy some?

443
00:23:54,725 --> 00:23:56,977
-I can go.
-The convenience store?

444
00:23:57,061 --> 00:24:00,272
-Do they sell curry there?
-Roux? They do.

445
00:24:00,356 --> 00:24:03,400
-They do?
-I need to go anyway, so I'll go too.

446
00:24:03,484 --> 00:24:05,694
-Would you mind?
-We'll buy some.

447
00:24:05,778 --> 00:24:06,779
Please.

448
00:24:06,862 --> 00:24:08,572
Thank you.

449
00:24:08,656 --> 00:24:09,657
Thank you.

450
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:14,244
Everyone seems nice.

451
00:24:14,328 --> 00:24:16,246
-I'm glad.
-They are.

452
00:24:16,330 --> 00:24:17,498
-Probably.
-Probably?

453
00:24:17,581 --> 00:24:18,916
I shouldn't talk about other people.

454
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:23,045
I wasn't sure if I could be friends.

455
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:27,883
-Why?
-I thought we might clash.

456
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:29,051
I wonder.

457
00:24:29,134 --> 00:24:31,804
-You never know.
-I guess we'll have to see.

458
00:24:31,887 --> 00:24:33,263
That's scary.

459
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,186
What do you think of her?

460
00:24:39,269 --> 00:24:40,729
Might not be my type.

461
00:24:40,854 --> 00:24:42,147
-For real?
-Yeah.

462
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:43,899
But I'm sure it'll be fun.

463
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:45,734
I seriously think...

464
00:24:46,735 --> 00:24:48,237
she's super cute.

465
00:24:48,320 --> 00:24:49,321
-Super cute?
-Yeah?

466
00:24:49,405 --> 00:24:50,406
Your type?

467
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:52,825
-She's pretty high energy.
-Yeah.

468
00:24:52,908 --> 00:24:54,410
I love that.

469
00:24:55,953 --> 00:24:57,037
Nice.

470
00:24:57,121 --> 00:25:00,666
But at least, in the worst case scenario,
I want someone with a nice rack.

471
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:04,169
Of which, there isn't, but...

472
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:06,296
-I like her.
-Her personality?

473
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:09,299
Her personality and face, too.

474
00:25:10,551 --> 00:25:13,470
It's nice that everyone eats together.

475
00:25:13,554 --> 00:25:15,514
Cheers!

476
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:18,267
-Glad to have you here.
-Thanks for having me.

477
00:25:20,436 --> 00:25:22,229
-I'm home.
-You surprised me.

478
00:25:22,354 --> 00:25:24,273
-Welcome back.
-Nice to meet you.

479
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:25,441
It's nice to meet you.

480
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:27,651
I moved in today.
I'm Misaki Tamori.

481
00:25:27,735 --> 00:25:28,861
I'm Arisa.

482
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:30,779
Welcome back.

483
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:32,823
