I'm impressed.

491
00:25:52,301 --> 00:25:53,552
It's good.

492
00:25:53,635 --> 00:25:55,721
So this must be better for you, Nacchan.

493
00:25:55,804 --> 00:25:57,848
-From your point of view.
-Really?

494
00:25:57,931 --> 00:26:00,601
-Arisa, you've really brightened up.
-Really?

495
00:26:00,684 --> 00:26:03,187
-Work is going well?
-Yeah.

496
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:05,522
-Same old?
-Yeah.

497
00:26:05,606 --> 00:26:07,775
-Is there anything we can do to help?
-Did you tan?

498
00:26:07,858 --> 00:26:09,443
I didn't.

499
00:26:09,526 --> 00:26:11,904
-It's hard to tan now.
-Um...

500
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:14,531
-Paint?
-It'd be nice if you could paint.

501
00:26:14,615 --> 00:26:17,242
At the place?
Paint what? Boxes?

502
00:26:17,326 --> 00:26:19,620
-Bricks and stuff.
-Bricks?

503
00:26:19,703 --> 00:26:21,413
Are you doing something?

504
00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:23,207
I'm putting on an exhibit in March.

505
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:25,417
-For hats?
-Yes.

506
00:26:25,501 --> 00:26:27,127
That's nice.

507
00:26:27,211 --> 00:26:28,712
Next week?

508
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:31,006
Yes, we're starting next week.

509
00:26:31,089 --> 00:26:34,092
-Let's go to help with the painting.
-Of course.

510
00:26:34,176 --> 00:26:37,137
-Can I use the <i>Terrace House</i> car?
-Yeah, I'm sure.

511
00:26:37,221 --> 00:26:39,014
I can drive.

512
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:41,433
-You can drive?
-Yeah.

513
00:26:41,517 --> 00:26:43,560
-Hikaru's driven us before.
-Yeah.

514
00:26:43,644 --> 00:26:45,312
A speed demon.

515
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:47,815
-I don't drive like that. Cut it out.
-That'd be scary.

516
00:26:47,898 --> 00:26:50,442
-I drive safely.
-You seem like you're a bad driver.

517
00:26:50,526 --> 00:26:52,820
-What?
-Bad?

518
00:26:52,903 --> 00:26:54,238
You're 18, right?

519
00:26:54,321 --> 00:26:56,907
I'm probably the best driver in the group.

520
00:26:56,990 --> 00:26:57,991
Well...

521
00:26:58,075 --> 00:27:00,536
-Have you been in the car with Arman?
-I have.

522
00:27:00,619 --> 00:27:01,787
-I'm good.
-He is good at it.

523
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:03,539
I don't know
what your definition of "good" is.

524
00:27:03,622 --> 00:27:04,623
It's normal.

525
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:07,167
Whatever.
I'm never driving you.

526
00:27:07,751 --> 00:27:09,086
Don't pout.

527
00:27:15,050 --> 00:27:16,468
When it piles up...

528
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:19,721
just drain it.

529
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:22,808
Wasn't Hikaru totally pissed?

530
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:24,601
What? About the driving?

531
00:27:24,685 --> 00:27:27,104
-I think he was mad.
-He was.

532
00:27:27,229 --> 00:27:29,523
-Was it scary?
-Yeah.

533
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:33,819
-I can't tell if he's serious or not.
-Yeah, it's hard to tell.

534
00:27:33,902 --> 00:27:35,696
It always seems like he's joking.

535
00:27:35,779 --> 00:27:38,615
-I did get a little scared.
-Yeah.

536
00:27:38,699 --> 00:27:41,118
Yeah, he was mad.

537
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:42,744
I wonder.

538
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:46,456
-Tamosan...
-Tamosan.

539
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,458
She reminds me of Asami Mizukawa.

540
00:27:48,542 --> 00:27:50,669
She is very frank
like an actress, Asami.

541
00:27:50,752 --> 00:27:52,296
ASAMI MIZUKAWA

542
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:55,757
It's good.
You like her right, Kentaro?

543
00:27:55,841 --> 00:27:56,925
Yes.

544
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:59,261
-What?
-Yes, she's interesting.

545
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:00,804
Go Kentaro, go!

546
00:28:02,639 --> 00:28:04,433
That lady there is dangerous.

547
00:28:06,351 --> 00:28:08,186
Don't listen to her.

548
00:28:09,271 --> 00:28:12,274
She really didn't need to say
that he seemed like a bad driver.

549
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:15,569
-Yeah, that wasn't good.
-Oh, it's bad.

550
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:19,281
-I thought maybe Hikaru would like that.
-Yeah.

551
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:20,449
Like it would fire him up.

552
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:21,533
Yes, yes...

553
00:28:23,243 --> 00:28:25,037
Listen, listen...

554
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:28,248
Not just you, Triendl,
but to all the female viewers.

555
00:28:28,332 --> 00:28:29,416
Yes.

556
00:28:29,499 --> 00:28:32,294
Men, of course, enjoy being teased...

557
00:28:32,377 --> 00:28:36,715
but not about their driving!

558
00:28:36,798 --> 00:28:37,799
You get it, right, Kentaro?

559
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:39,343
-You're 18.
-I totally understand.

560
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:41,136
I see.

561
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:45,057
Driving is an essential part
of being a man.

562
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:46,975
It's special.

563
00:28:47,476 --> 00:28:52,356
So, if you're told you're bad at it,
it's very demeaning.

564
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:54,650
He was pretty pissed.

565
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:56,026
He was like, "What?"

566
00:28:56,109 --> 00:28:58,278
And to be told that
in front of everyone...

567
00:28:58,362 --> 00:29:00,781
They just met.

568
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:02,950
-Yeah, so driving...
-So, it's bad.

569
00:29:03,033 --> 00:29:04,409
Better to leave it alone.

570
00:29:04,493 --> 00:29:07,454
Especially coming from a girl
he's interested in.

571
00:29:07,537 --> 00:29:10,332
-It's shocking.
-Yeah, there's definitely that.

572
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,668
Yeah, it was bad timing.

573
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,169
That expression...

574
00:29:15,379 --> 00:29:20,259
From a female point of view,
does that turn you off?

575
00:29:20,342 --> 00:29:24,137
-Is this worth apologizing about?
-No.

576
00:29:24,221 --> 00:29:25,555
That might hurt his pride more.

577
00:29:25,639 --> 00:29:27,641
To say, "I'm sorry I said
you looked like you'd be a bad driver."

578
00:29:29,434 --> 00:29:31,103
"It's fine."

579
00:29:31,186 --> 00:29:33,438
-Crying?
-Yes, crying.

580
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:35,691
"No one's ever said that
about my driving."

581
00:29:37,067 --> 00:29:40,862
-We've got the new guy coming.
-Yes, we do.

582
00:29:40,946 --> 00:29:44,866
Dreams for the future?
We haven't asked that yet.

583
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:46,535
-An amusement park.
-She said that earlier.

584
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:48,287
-Arisa didn't hear.
-An amusement park?

585
00:29:48,370 --> 00:29:50,414
-To build one?
-Yes.

586
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:54,960
-Wow, like a Disneyland?
-Yes.

587
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:57,879
Then, I'll build you a hat store, too.

588
00:29:57,963 --> 00:30:00,090
What? For me?

589
00:30:00,173 --> 00:30:01,508
Inside the park?

590
00:30:03,885 --> 00:30:07,180
-An amusement park of everyone's dreams.
-That's right!

591
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:10,183
-I see.
-I'll build one for you.

592
00:30:10,267 --> 00:30:12,144
For her?

593
00:30:21,445 --> 00:30:22,654
Plans for tomorrow?

594
00:30:24,281 --> 00:30:25,657
-Off?
-Off.

595
00:30:25,741 --> 00:30:27,409
Off tomorrow?

596
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:28,493
What about you, Arisa?

597
00:30:28,577 --> 00:30:31,121
I have work,
but I'll be home early Sunday.

598
00:30:31,204 --> 00:30:32,205
What about you, Nacchan?

599
00:30:32,289 --> 00:30:33,957
-I'm off tomorrow.
-No way!

600
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:35,125
Really.

601
00:30:35,208 --> 00:30:37,586
-Did you show her room?
-Not yet.

602
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:38,920
Why don't you show her?

603
00:30:41,423 --> 00:30:43,091
No way!

604
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:44,176
Seriously?

605
00:30:45,302 --> 00:30:47,596
-At this time?
-Arman, let's go see the guy.

606
00:30:49,139 --> 00:30:50,223
Really?

607
00:30:52,267 --> 00:30:53,352
Yes?

608
00:30:53,435 --> 00:30:55,270
<i>I'm moving in today.</i>

609
00:30:55,354 --> 00:30:57,522
-Come in.
<i>-Okay.</i>

610
00:31:05,364 --> 00:31:07,491
I'm really nervous for some reason.

611
00:31:07,574 --> 00:31:09,785
Maybe because it's so sudden.

612
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:13,413
-Wow.
-What do you mean, "wow"?

613
00:31:13,497 --> 00:31:15,791
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

